pan><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/8/02 3:41:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1311.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm thinking about starting a character</span><hr size=1> Rile <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>I'm probably &quot;sticking my foot in it,&quot; but I think the general consensus is that &quot;thees, thous, and thys&quot; aren't necessary here, but you will find others who use (sometimes badly, but honestly enough) thees and thous.<br><br>There have been threads upon threads about this very topic here at FV's home away from home message board - flamed, crisped, and burnt, as well as thought out, considerate, and mature.<br><br>I have heard of RPing guilds who strictly enforce RP in interactions with other players, but being ok with ooc in guild chat *only.*  There are some that are geared towards 100% RP at all times.  Then there are the &quot;live-and-let-live&quot; players and guilds.<br><br>I think that you will do just fine if you aren't a &quot;d00d joo r0x0r (whatever the heck that means)&quot; kind of player.  Just be yourself, and be wise and respectful to the fact that some players are 100% immersed, and you should be ok.<br><br>I've only personally had only one incident my whole time here that I was criticised in-game (in front of all my guildies, no less) for calling a Dark Elf a &quot;Drow.&quot;  (How that did wonders to sharpen my blooming rp skills.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  What about that?  I laughed and got on with other things.  (I shoulda said, &quot;I didn't say you were a Drow, I said you are a schmoe!&quot; Lol)<br><br>Ack... I've distracted myself...<br><br>May I add that I thought that it was such a beautiful site to run throught the Commons/Ro tunnel the first time and see NO ONE there.  That was sweeeeeeet!<br><br>Come play with us.  Your history will be made as you go.  You will find kindred spirits with whom to make friends.  I'm horrible at D&amp;D, but just try to remember what it was like to pretend when you were a kid, and you will be fine.<br><br>Welcome to FV, should you decide to venture in and take a peek <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p><p align="center"><font color="#E1B500"><b><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=98751"><i><font size="2" color="#E1B500">ÆoniiElysium<br></font></i></a></b><a href="http://members.tripod.com/immortalkindred"><font size="1" color="#E1B500">~*~An Immortal Kindred ~*~</font></a></font></p><p align="center"><font size="1" color="#E1B500">Jyleel</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/8/02 6:08:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1311.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm thinking about starting a character</span><hr size=1> Just as long as you do not habitually say the words &quot;Hail and well met&quot; ..... we will get along fine. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br>a_orc_pawn says: &quot;Hail and well met, puny Human! Thou hast spoilt your own lands! Thou shalt no