ing buying second, third, fourth, etc. accounts, so make sure your choice is something you enjoy.<br><br>Aeonii:<br><br>Frankly, that dark elf's response seems ridiculous to me.  There really is only one source for dark elves, and that's TSR's drow (also called &quot;dark elves&quot;).  Like EverQuest's dark elves, drow are white-haired and dark-blue/black-skinned.  Almost invariably, they're represented as having been twisted versions of their light cousins, 'stolen' by an evil deity.  R.A. Salvatore's Drizz't novels come right out of TSR's Forgotten Realms (in fact, the first one, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>The Crystal Shard</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, was the second TSR novel).<br><br>EQ's &quot;dark elves&quot; are so close to TSR's &quot;drow elves&quot;, I'm surprised there wasn't a copyright violation lawsuit.<br><br>To chastize you for calling him a &quot;drow elf&quot; seems silly.<br><br>Lasgalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1311.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1311.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1311.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.firiona-vie.com/images/arfv.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.threadControl?topicID=1311.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1311.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pu